(264, '2021-08-28 13:58:12', 'auds ', 'sherylyang2002@gmail.com', 'The thing about IMU being a small campus is that you get to meet more friends and build better connections compared to other unis (in the health sciences field). \r\nFacilities are meh, because of it being so small, but still exist and can be used. Computers are great. Library is small, but the computer labs and common spaces are more than enough to accommodate your needs. And with all the cafes available around Sri Petaling and Bukit Jalil, you don\'t have to worry about it too much. Lecturers in foundation are great, they care a lot about feedback and are quick to change or amend things according to student\'s suggestions, at least those valid and within reason ofc . Management is good, and quick to respond to students.The fees are also okay cause you get 50% bursary if you progress to IMU\'S UG (dk if it still applies now, do make ur own research before signing up).\r\n', 'Foundation in Science', 2020, 36, 3, 4, 5, 3, 5, 1, NULL),
(265, '2021-08-28 15:34:24', 'Weebish_DJ ', 'juniorwong5321@gmail.com', 'This university has probably the best environment in the country imo. The facilities here are quite new, maybe its because its still a relatively new uni. Lecturers for my course are great for most of the time. The hostels are also extremely cheap for what they\'re offering. There\'s AC and a built in toilet with water heaters. The downside is that the rooms are a little bit cramped but hey, at least its better than the dorms in public universities. Coughs*\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, the management of the varsity is less to be desired. Let\'s just say they\'re cold blooded with no compassion. They can be very authoritarian sometimes so I just leave it here. The food sold at the cafeteria is also quite expensive and there\'s only a stall selling halal food. So for Muslim students, that can be quite inconvenient. \r\n\r\nOther than the management, XMUM is actually a very beautiful and good university. \r\n\r\n', 'Bachelors Degree in Journalism ', 2020, 114, 4, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1, NULL);
