(266, '2021-08-29 17:12:41', 'Veron', 'veron020529@hotmail.com', 'IMU is a good choice for those who are interested in becoming a health professional.The lecturers there are super kind to help students especially when we face some problems in our study.The hostel for IMU is also quite near from the university.Thus it is quite convenient to go to school every day.', 'Foundation In Science', 2021, 36, 3, 3, 5, 4, 3, 1, NULL),
(267, '2021-08-29 17:38:35', 'Minnn', 'chuminnn18@gmail.com', 'In short,IMU is eligibe to be consider as your first choice if you are considering to further your studies overseas.IMU has a complete studying system they have well qualified lectures.Their performances during the start of the pandemic was well too,improvements are needed but as part of the first response they had did their best. ', 'Foundation in science', 2020, 36, 4, 3, 5, 4, 4, 1, NULL),
(268, '2021-08-29 22:35:14', 'Ouroboros', 'duckmarshal123@gmail.com', 'The lecturers are pretty good to be honest. The unfortunate part is that the facilities at Help University (Elm/Damansara) are quite...inadequate. \r\n\r\nOne nice factor is that the MRT is just nearby so transportation is convenient. If you\'re planning to study IT at Help, you won\'t be going to the Damansara campus but the Subang one.\r\n\r\nThe library is quite small and staying there for more than an hour will probably freeze your fingers off. The food has improved since a year back. \r\n\r\nDon\'t expect much of a campus life if you study here, what with the disappointing facilities and all. Nearly all of the clubs and societies are located at Help University Subang. \r\n\r\n', 'Diploma in IT', 2019, 40, 3, 3, 4, 3, 3, 1, NULL),
(269, '2021-08-29 22:59:35', 'Oreo monster ', 'claudiacwc@gmail.com', 'I think IMU is smaller than I thought, not the grand university I have in mind since itâ€™s quite expensive. The facilities are old and the labs are barely renovated. I remember regretting why I didnâ€™t choose other universities when I joined the campus tour. Management-wise, I am definitely disappointed and sometimes annoyed by their speed. They take a long time just to give the unconditional offer. [The admissions department does a great job when you first join.] For their e-learning portals, itâ€™s functional but there are rooms for improvement when it comes to its layout and design. \r\n\r\nAll that is left to love in IMU is the people. The â€˜peopleâ€™ here refers to peers, helpful seniors or juniors who just joined. If I am to go back in time, Iâ€™ll still choose IMU because of the friends I cherished in FiS. They provided me with healthy competition and a lovely environment for me to learn and meet different people. I also know if seniors who are really helpful and friendly. \r\n\r\nIf you are planning to take the PMS track (2 years in IMU and then remaining years in partner universities), then you can consider studying in IMU. If you are choosing a local track (MBBS), remember to seek for more advice and see for yourself whether this is the right university for you. ', 'Foundation in Science (FiS)  ', 2020, 36, 3, 3, 4, 4, 3, 1, NULL),
(270, '2021-08-29 23:12:02', 'Jojooo', 'ongjosephine@hotmail.com', 'IMU is definitely smaller compared to other universities, it was not something I had pictured but it gives the warm comforting feeling. Facilities wise, it is quite good especially the library and the numerous locations to study in campus. The wifi is excellent as well perfect for online classes. The food is nice, though a little pricey for an outstation student. However, due to MCO a lot of food vendors are not available during dinner time which is inconvenient to hostel students. The environment can be quite competitive but the students are extremely friendly, lecturers as well. The management is not the best and have room for improvement. Overall a good place to study health sciences and would highly recommend it! ', 'Foundation in Science (FIS)', 2020, 36, 4, 5, 5, 3, 3, 1, NULL),
