(300, '2021-09-02 11:30:46', 'Anon', '198271@student.upm.edu.my', 'Facilities:\r\nThe facilities I think is average.\r\nPro:\r\n1) Basically basic necessities are available\r\n\r\nCons:\r\n1) Bus ride sometimes can be chaotic during peak hours. You really have to cramp in order to get in bus or wait another 15 minutes. Sometimes walking back to college is faster than taking the bus\r\n2) Sport facilities / Stadium located a bit far away from college. The nearest college is about 700m away. Although bus will stop near stadium, but you still have to walk for a distance. For the sport lovers such as gym goers this could be troublesome place to go for sports. \r\n3) Wifi connection can be very bad in some area which to some extent even the lecturer were also feed up with the wifi\r\n\r\nEnvironment:\r\nPro\r\n1) Full of green and got a lot of beautiful parks for leisure activities\r\n2) The ladang near the stadium is very beautiful and worth to visit\r\n\r\nLecture\r\nPro\r\n1) Most lecturer (that I met) are friendly and approachable\r\nCons\r\n2) Some lecturer or course outline may makes you question your existence. \r\n\r\nFood\r\nPro\'s\r\n1) There are some good food stall that one can visit such as Chillax from KPZ\r\n2) Outside the campus there are a lot of restaurants, food stall or mamak to try\r\nCon\'s\r\n1) If you are not get used to Malay food, you might having some hard time to fulfill your hunger\r\n2) Some food stall owners just rip the money out of your wallet. Sometimes eating outside is slightly cheaper\r\n3) Since the Covid-19 some food court has become dirty as if no one were maintaining it\r\n\r\nManagement\r\nPro\'s\r\n1) Some staff were friendly and approachable\r\nCon\'s\r\n1) If you were being unlucky, you will be a part of bola sepak game where your enquiry will being \"kicked\" from one place to another\r\n2) Poor Covid-19 support for student. Always take long time to make decisive action.\r\nYes, there is some refund for students but only RM34