(359, '2021-09-19 16:36:13', 'Zzzzä½ çˆ±æˆ‘æˆ‘çˆ±ä½ èœœé›ªå†°åŸç”œèœœèœœ', 'fahf@gmail.com', 'In FACT, HWUM (Heriot-Watt Uni Malaysia) is still a new school if compared to other uni. Talking about the facilities, most of them is very new and convenient. Student Centre is always there ready to help students with their issues such as enrolment or payment issues. Also, there are clubs or societies like boxing, dancing etc. , as well as resting rooms equipped with simple games such as pools, ping pong, darts etc. Also, the library is comfortable with self-service book borrowing machine. \r\nTalking about the environment, the best thing is that it is  a nice surrounding to communicate in English. This will force people to improve their speaking and writing skills to have a better communication. The surrounding is still cool for a new uni like HWUM. However, don\'t forget that it is at Putrajaya, it is not so developed and convenient as KL. For HWUM, bus service is provided directly to a few accommodation site (but it takes longer time than a car). If you wish to visit other place, u might need to take the public transport (If you are not familiar with the public transport/ not familiar with the payment/ time doesn\'t match for the schedule, u can only take taxi from MyCar & Grab. Not cheap thooo, especially when u\'re late and missed the school bus hahahhah). AND, since it is not so developed, most of the buildings are gov. building, not so much shopping centre as KL. Most of the food outside of Uni is Malay/ Islamic, followed by Indian and the least is Chinese food. (I\'m just telling what I observed, so you have to get used to it). \r\nTalking about lecture, first of all u have to admit that there are always good and bad lecturers in every school, so I\'m not commenting on that. For current pandemic, HWUM is delivering through online lectures, and enables mixing of Face2face and online lectures if the situation allows. So, what I felt for my course is that, its standard is quite high above the average, quite difficult and worth to study. However, don\'t forget that it a \"branch\" of the Edinburgh HW uni, together with Dubai HW. U can expect for a troublesome schedule, especially when something happened. I will talk about this on MANAGEMENT. \r\nTalking about food, hah, one thing, nice to eat but EXPENSIVE. This is talking about the uni canteen! RM1.5 for a plate of rice, RM 2 for a scoop of vege, RM 3 for a scoop of (non-vege) if I\'m not mistaken; and the quantity is not satisfying sometimes. For drinks, I don\'t think RM 2 or 3 can get a cup of coffee... If you are used to eat cheaper food, then you might ... IN short, the variation of food and drinks is there, but avg price is higher with respect to the quantity, even if compared with Genting Staff canteen. \r\nMANAGEMENT. About the troublesome schedule, when something happens, it takes time to have a so called \"international discussion\" with Edinburgh and Dubai uni. For example the pandemic recently, I can say, HWUM is almost the last school in Malaysia (from what I compared with other uni) to cancel Face2Face class, not until someone wrote to the Provost a.k.a CEO of HWUM, urging Provost to deal with it. I\'m staying at an accommodation (not HWUM\'s), and what I experienced is every student from other school left already, leaving me alone at the accommodation. If I\'m not wrong, the school\'s announcement (on cancelling the F2F session) is very/ extremely near to the gov\'s announcement on 1st MCO. I don\'t know whether it is due to the trouble in discussing with other campus (Edinburgh & Dubai), whether the school management don\'t wish to afford the Income deficit OR whether they can\'t predict the adverse impact (meanwhile,  the China cases was rising wildly). On the other side, about setting academic schedules, it is troublesome to have discussion always with other campus, while my friend at uni like UTAR has FIXED(very fixed) schedule from the beginning of semester. HWUM\'s announcement on the date of assignments, examinations etc. always take time.... and was amended quite frequently to match with other campus. Also one thing I hate the most, SOME lecturers love to upload the slides right before or after the lecture sessions. How ppl gonna study or refer? How ppl gonna discover some doubts before the lecture? It is better now, to have pre-recorded videos for online studies. Hah, one thing I almost missed out. The tuition fees. To be honest, not cheap tho (For UG Mechanical Engineering is like 40k smtg, PG is like 50k smtg, do go and check at the school website). And somemore after the outbreak of virus, the school management insisted on maintaining the original amount of tuition fees (as they claim that students are still using the facilities), meanwhile other uni are reducing the fees for their students. So, è§ä»è§æ™ºï¼Œyou can still choose HWUM if you can afford this. \r\nOne more thing, students and staffs of HWUM are very friendly. They are nice to students. Also if you left something (for me like laptop or textbooks), you might find it on the original location or get it back from the Lost and Found. Yet, if you\'re currently suffering to stay at Putrajaya, do go to Putrajaya Sentral and take the train to KL. ESCAPEEEEE hahah.\r\n', 'MEng Mechanical Engineering', 2019, 111, 5, 3, 3, 3, 2, 1, '210.186.109.32'),
