(381, '2021-09-19 20:06:06', 'Single boy', 'jrn1904833@xmu.edu.my', 'Like what you saw about how beautiful is the environment of Xiamen University Malaysia, at least I can guarantee you it is real. All the facilities are open for use to every student, include the gym, courts, track&field, pool, and library. They also built with hostel within the campus area for students at a price that is more affordable compare to the outsides. However, some facilities are just with fine exterior and another one, I don\'t know the reason, the studio room that is not open for campus students. As well as the A3 library that said will be open and start operating by the end of the year every year I asked.\r\n\r\nTheir lecturers are equipped with professional skills and experience but not all of them have good teaching skills. All lecturers who had taught me are kind and willing to help the students. However, I have some friends who are not as lucky as me. Some lecturer might have their own accent, so it took more attention to follow what they taught.\r\n\r\nWe have a variety of choices of food here, although some are expensive. Nearby also have Mamak stall and Econsave within 10 minutes of car distance.\r\n\r\nFinally the management, it is not like how you be treated during the open day. Some office workers just did not do their job well. There are several times I submit documents but the office worker did not mention all the details that I have to fill in. The incident had caused me to face serious consequences. The workers do not have professional values and ethics in their job. Students ourselves have to stay alert with all the documents we filled in ourselves. Based on what I had experienced, their management is holding back the fame of Xiamen University.', 'Mass Communication', 2018, 114, 4, 5, 5, 4, 2, 1, '42.190.214.67'),
