(398, '2021-09-19 23:44:41', 'CS student 101', 'cloud8454@hotmail.com', 'If there is no MCO and you want uni-life definitely come to kampar the environment here is 10/10 and food is nice too. If you have a car, you can consider rent a better place than Westlake haha. Join more activity there is really a lot of activity I bet there will definitely be one which is suitable for you.\r\n------------------------------------------\r\nIn terms of study, do expect a tight schedule and hard academic life since you know, this is utar. ps: carefully choose your teammate BECAREFUL!\r\n\r\nIf you are considering CS but you are more to development job like mobile app, web app, native app, go either to IA or IB don\'t choose CS. Once you choose CS most of the lecturers will put a high standard on you, they always say sh*t like \"you are a cs student you are expected to be better\". If in the end you still want CS, do an AI-related FYP if you want a higher grade, basically, if you go for development path in CS, your course structure will similar to IA.', 'Computer Science', 2019, 2, 4, 5, 3, 4, 3, 1, '14.192.212.191'),
(399, '2021-09-19 23:45:09', 'Passer by', 'koharuyouka@gmail.com', 'All the comments here are the situation of the school before the 2020 lockdown, probably there will be some differences or changes now, so just take it as a reference.\r\n\r\nThe facilities here are quite okay, but it can be better because it is really difficult to travel outside if you don\'t own your own transport. They got the gym, pool, field, but the main library building is not yet finished (and I heard that they keep saying will finish by the end of the year for a few years already...), therefore, we currently only have a temporarily small library.\r\n\r\nI think you can really take a good picture here, but somehow many places are still under construction so there\'s still some pollution here (noise and water pollution). And personally,I think that it is not that important to have good scenery to study :P. If you talk about the studying environment, I think the class is quite nice, with powerful air cons and many halls (but this is not the same for the computer lab, I will slightly mention later). I\'m not the person who likes to go to the library as it is really stressful to see people studying and somehow makes me even more distracting, so I prefer to lock inside the hostel and read by my own. So I think I won\'t comment much on this.\r\n\r\nFor the lecturers, I think it is just a matter of luck whether you can meet a good lecturer. I can only say maybe some of them are really professional in the field, but they may not have good teaching skills. But in the end, you have to learn things by yourself anyway.\r\n\r\nThere are some stores that sell food at a much cheaper price, like the mixed rice and ban mee, but the rest I think is quite.... or very expensive. (the rest cost you RM 6 and above). And due to the pandemic, I heard that many stores have closed now.\r\n\r\nThe management I think I don\'t need to comment for now, just read other comments I think you will know :D\r\n\r\nTalk about our course, TBH I do not recommend taking DMT here because I personally feel that they did not put much attention on us. Resources provided for us are quite limited, like the VR headsets it is really insufficient for the whole class. The school computers provided to us are actually not powerful enough to support rendering, which makes computers always brokes and makes other people unable to use them. The computer lab is also not 24 hours open, therefore, it is quite inconvenient if you are rushing for some big projects. I\'m not sure whether this is the same for others, but somehow we have a semester with 7 subjects, and most of them are project-based, so it was a hell semester for us. But if you can overcome it, the experience is yours.\r\n\r\nAnd please notice that the grading here is not the same as other uni in Malaysia. 85 and above are A (GPA 4.0), 80-84 is A- (GPA 3.7), 75-79 is B (GPA 3.3), 70-74 is (GPA 3.0), and so on. So you can see that there is a weird gap for the GPA of A- and B, and this can make your CGPA drop significantly if you can\'t get 80 and above. They even have a quota for people who can get A in a subject. Therefore, you really need to work very hard to get better marks.\r\n\r\nOverall, this is still a very new uni as it was just established for a few years only. Many things still need to be improved. Maybe it will be better in the future, but now I think maybe just research for more uni first before choosing here.', 'Digital Media Technology', 2018, 114, 4, 4, 4, 3, 1, 1, '115.134.113.92'),
(400, '2021-09-19 23:55:07', 'Gwyneth Lee', 'leezhithong@gmail.com', 'Overall Lecturer are good, but only few of them have their problem. \r\nThe most important is the management is sucks! \r\nOverall is fine only the management problems. Hence, please think before you join.', 'Bachelor degree of Business', 2020, 96, 4, 4, 3, 4, 1, 1, '14.1.240.95'),
