(410, '2021-09-20 09:43:31', 'Scholarship Holder', 'myboypreniscute@gmail.com', 'Facility:\r\nFor media production and broadcasting tbh, our facilities are outstanding compared to other schools in PG, Radio studio, audio studio, sadly our shooting equipment we have quite a number, but its all donated from broadcasting graduates after their screening. Not the right way for the school to get stg though.\r\nPretty shitty thing is our facility fees are 4k per enrollment, however nothing much has changed over the years in terms of wifi, canteen, improvement of air conditioned rooms. Chinese studies block have difficulty accessing the wifi, toilets that just changed to 3 cubicles per floor for block C per floor per gender and have no toilet paper, parking is quite a long walk away etc. The enhancement on the looks in terms of web interface and school compound and thats about it.\r\n\r\nEnvironment:\r\nFriendly lecturers, happy school compound, everyone and everything looks nice and colourful, have big potential and connections for all students towards the industry etc.\r\n\r\nLecture:\r\nWell depends on the lecturer basically. Lecturers like Dr Yang Jie, Mr Prakash, Mr Arif, Mr Zhariff, Mr Lim Tse Shaun, Ms Ooi Li Fang, Mr Eswandy, and a few more actually a lot of lecturers that I cant remember they are amazing and brilliant in a lot of ways and will help you so much. As for a few others, a bit hard to deal with or sometimes make no sense, but just a few of them that should beware la\r\n\r\nFood:\r\nAwful. There\'s nothing in HCUC canteen except tidbits biscuits, drinks etc. Han City, sundry shop in Han Chiang Stadium which sells fruits and a lot lot more other tidbits, ice cream and stuff is way better. HCUC Canteen aunty will get mad at u because u go to Han Chiang High School canteen and bring their foos to HCUC canteen. They even lock the door to Han Chiang High School so that u can have their food, which is often undercooked, not even tasty, eat only when desperate, rather eat outside food court come back. Like what? We pay facility fees for this canteen to not get a new vendor? Lol.\r\n\r\nManagement:\r\nThem looking into the facility fees and giving unreasonable excuses in the official letters for us, is very questionable and suspicious. Only rm100 deduction for one sem that I wasn\'t even involved in because I finished diploma ady that time. Since then no deduction already. HCUC student kena before that the student services dismiss her problems complaining facility fees, and then she ask for a proper reply dy but then they \"ghost\" her, then she posted it on social media and then I saw in comment section that management threaten her. Src compile feedback regarding this issue ady and then management still dont want to deduct anything even 50 or 100rm. Pfft. Overall u see our facilities, canteen etc ady, u know that the management probably can\'t hear you from the top... Hahaha', 'Bachelor of Communication (Media Production) (Hons)', 2021, 88, 2, 4, 3, 1, 1, 1, '42.189.172.93'),
(412, '2021-09-20 10:37:34', 'Kent Mok', 'kentmok85@gmail.com', 'Overall is good, but sometimes the assignment questions are nonsense, and the standard of marking assignment is different, the mark/ grade will be getting better result after appeal. ', 'Bachelor Degree of Business Admin', 2018, 37, 4, 4, 3, 3, 4, 1, '113.211.190.38'),
(413, '2021-09-20 10:52:43', 'Chan Kar Man', 'chankm606@gmail.com', 'AM is probably the least assignment programme you can ever find in UTAR. That is, if you study pure math related elective courses and when pandemic isn\'t a thing. Can\'t guarantee for other elective courses though. \r\n\r\nAll the lecturers that I have met are really nice. \r\n\r\nIf you are interested in mathematics, welcome. Best to figure out your interested area of maths before your FYP year. Else, you\'ll suffer.', 'Bachelor of Science (Hons) Applied Mathematics with Computing', 2021, 1, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 1, '118.100.212.205'),
