(429, '2021-09-20 13:07:33', 'umt alumni-ng', 'ngjyesze@gmail.com', 'Good environment near to sea side, good place to study and relax as there don\'t have a lot of entertainment. \r\nThe campus is quite new and the whole campus are able to reach within walking distance. You can also enjoy the sea breeze, view of sea and sound of waves at anytime. The lecture hall is also comfortable with all of them are a/c, and friendly lecturers and staffs. However, the choice of food is not much due to the rural area. But, you can still get a lot of good food outside the campus. ', 'Food Science (Food Service and Nutrition)', 2013, 31, 5, 5, 4, 3, 4, 1, '118.100.11.106'),
(430, '2021-09-20 13:17:21', 'Anonymous', 'lim.joanne0131@gmail.com', 'The lecturers are all very dedicated and helpful. Especially during this pandemic.All classes are conducted online, however, the lecturers are very responsive.', 'Master of Human Resource Management', 2021, 7, 5, 5, 5, 3, 5, 1, '175.145.228.36'),
(431, '2021-09-20 13:25:31', 'David', 'dianqing99@gmail.com', 'Things would be perfect if there are no MCO, I\'m glad that I\'m still able to enjoy 3 years of Uni life in Kampar and I savor every bit of it. \r\n\r\n\r\nThe environment is serene and quiet, perfect for study nerd like me. However there isn\'t as much entertainment that you would expect if you study in Sungai Long campus. Transportation wise isn\'t a problem. but a car would be better for grocery shopping duties. \r\n\r\nI\'m going to echo what other have said in this page. Don\'t expect a easy ride if you come to UTAR. Be a contributing member and don\'t drag your teammates down. Don\'t expect spoon feeding from your lecturer as you need to do extra learning on your own in order to score a good grade. The lectures that provided are aim as a starting point for further discussion. So don\'t be surprised if your classmate seem to be further ahead in the pack in terms of knowledge. \r\n\r\nAbout IA vs CS, IA is more development/IT/Database where as CS is more towards the theoretical (Complexity analysis, Big Data Analysis, AI and so on) if you are going to join CS, A healthy dose of Maths is going to help you alot. Make sure you check the course structure as they are some subjects like deep learning and data sciences that are only taught in CS degree where IA is more focus on Database/Development.\r\n\r\nFacilities wise in FICT, It\'s adequate, Some labs have been upgraded slowly so it\'s usable. But you can only use it during class hour. I think FICT have a little bit of catching up on facilities (As evident they have been upgrading their lab + new Big Data Lab during the MCO period). However it would be better if there\'s a maker space where students are free to tinker with Raspi, MCU, Distributing Computing where Lecturer and Students could work on research project/Side project together.    ', 'Information System Engineering', 2021, 2, 4, 5, 3, 5, 4, 1, '175.144.64.135'),
(432, '2021-09-20 13:29:48', 'Help Comm Student', 'joelliew281@gmail.com', 'Help Comm department is placed in Wisma Help, search it up and if it feels like an abandoned building. Yup, that\'s the place you\'re gonna spend 3 years at. \r\nThe facilities for comm department are also extremely old and bad. \r\nThe lecturers also varies. Some are good some are speechless. \r\nIMO, Help is not the best choice to study communications at. It is totally not worth it for the fees u\'re paying. \r\nI regret my choice ngl. \r\nThe only good thing is the people in  Wisma Help are quite friendly and a lot of food trucks near the building. ', 'Bachelor in Marketing Comm', 2019, 40, 1, 3, 3, 5, 2, 1, '14.192.213.20'),
(433, '2021-09-20 13:40:38', 'SIMHS', 'greenishshan@gmail.com', 'I just rate the quality of lecture base on my course. The overall of UTM activities such as utmxcite, club&society, and the living hostel environment was satisfying me. By the way, I like the logo design from UTM. ', 'Property Management (FABU) ', 2021, 4, 3, 5, 2, 3, 2, 1, '175.142.26.38'),
