(453, '2021-09-20 18:12:52', 'Senior from Utar Sg Long', 'cz@1utar.my', 'If you trust that Utar provides the \"Best\" education and \"Lowest\" Tuition fees in the whole Malaysia. then you are damm wrong. The lecturer here are just read the slide.. thats all. and the fees also included alot of hidden fees that will not show on brochure at first. Trust me, if you do you research properly, you will find some other college or uni that come with 6 Star rating but lower tuition fees than utar. Talking about management, if you believe that your review towards lecturer will be check by those management, then you are damm wrong. They just collect the survey for the sake of doing it only. The management also very lansi, if you trying to ask a question, our ask them to solve a problem for you, they will just take their own sweet time and ignore it, you rush them, they tell you, \"Utar did not lack of student, you choose Utar, follow Utar style, not happy, Withdraw\" Anyhow I already graduated. Good luck!', 'Foundation', 2017, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, '14.192.209.141'),
(454, '2021-09-20 18:13:01', 'Leonard', 'leonard970207@gmail.com', 'Management is good\r\nFood is variety\r\nTransport is nice also, can go to ECM or Berjaya Megamall\r\nSave the hustle from crowding in Klang Valley (like traffic jam)\r\nLecturers are nice as well\r\n\r\nPS: If you choose to study engineering, choose UMP. Don\'t choose anywhere else. UMP is a public uni, which means the tuition fees are cheap if eligible.', 'BA (Hons) Mechanical Engineering', 2017, 17, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 1, '115.164.216.199'),
