(457, '2021-09-20 19:58:34', 'Michelle', 'xueminlok2598@gmail.com', 'As a pharmacy graduate, I will say that the teaching and learning process is enjoyable. Although the syllabus is quite burdened due to the course itself, the lecturer are always ready to guide you. That\'s why I rate 5-stars there. However, USM management is poor. Numbers of management problem, including fees, accommodation and facilities are consistently arising during my study. ', 'Pharmacy', 2017, 20, 3, 4, 5, 4, 2, 1, '42.189.94.209'),
(458, '2021-09-20 20:33:44', 'Hi210918', 'ivvyyyyy@gmail.com', 'Quality lecturers are definitely the core for a school/college/uni. From my perspective, BAC lecturers are of high quality and professional. Lecture notes   are equally good and while pair with good lecturer thatâ€™s where the best combo that you can ever had. ', 'Law and CLP', 2018, 119, 4, 4, 5, 3, 3, 1, '218.111.175.204'),
(459, '2021-09-20 21:01:28', 'Some Graduated Architecture Boi', 'qizhi2009@live.com.my', 'Spent 4 years studying here from diploma to degree, the lecturers are pretty passionate and knowledgeable, lectures are informative. Students are somehow balanced among all race which allows you to mix with different people.\r\n\r\nThe studio for Architecture degree (Architecture Diploma are using old studio which are pretty horrible) are considerably new, internet are ok but sometimes slow. Most of the buildings and facilities are decades old and very poorly managed, especially the old buildings. \r\n\r\nAs for students who are staying inside, it is pretty convenient as there is grocery store, stationary and printing store in the compound but price are higher and lower quality compare to outside for printing. Food choice were not much especially healthy foods is almost non-existence.', 'Bachelor\'s Degree in Architecture', 2018, 62, 2, 3, 4, 1, 1, 1, '202.190.123.112'),
(460, '2021-09-20 21:07:59', 'Emily Cheah', 'emily.yithung0611@gmail.com', 'TBH, the module outlines are well planned. You might not realise this until you go for an internship and have to compete with others. Facilities for engineering department are well-equipped,with quality lecturers. ', 'Chemical with Environmental Engineering', 2023, 112, 4, 5, 5, 4, 4, 1, '192.228.137.155'),
(461, '2021-09-20 21:12:35', 'Jason Koh', 'emily.yithung0611@gmail.com', 'The module outlines are badly planned which other unis learned these modules when they\'re in Year 1/2 but we study it only when we are Year 3. Didn\'t manage to \"enjoy\" this uni much as the lecturers have no experience in conducting proper lecturers. In the end, I had to retake my foundation, then UG since the uni I went to doesn\'t accredit my foundation in UTP.', 'Chemical Engineering', 2023, 52, 5, 2, 1, 1, 1, 1, '192.228.137.155'),
