(480, '2021-09-21 19:13:09', 'Sampah Artwork', 'mediaguy2017@gmail.com', 'Okay, breakdown. I think facilities wise in Faculty of Creative Multimedia. They almost got everything. There\'s a depot where you can borrow equipment such as Zoom H4, Blackmagic Cam, etc for your video production needs. Mocap studios for the 3D guys. Sound recording studio and if you can\'t manage to book the studio. You can always borrow the Scarlett Studio set to do your recording session at your dorm. Newly added FX Lab are equipped with pretty decent machine that can run 3D softwares smoothly. \r\n\r\nHowever... Environment wise, I think it\'s pretty dilapidated because it\'s been 20 years old... and it seems like this Faculty isn\'t in the best interest of MMU so it don\'t get much renovation compared to other faculty. Also the forever unfixed elevator... huh huh\r\n\r\nAbout the lecture/lecturer, without a doubt they are knowledgeable and some of them really put extra effort to make sure the students are okay. Always ready to help, but under one condition which is you yourself are willing to learn. Some of the theory class can be extremely boring though. \r\n\r\nWhat\'s more to say about Food in Faculty of Creative Multimedia? FCM Cafe food best lah, the ayam goreng, maggie goreng, paling best and most of all, they are freaking affordable, definitely below market price if you go dine in outside of campus in Cyberjaya. When you get sick of FCM cafe food, you can always go for a switch in Deen Cafe which is just a walking distance away. My favorite dish is their Nasi Goreng Paprik. Flavor and pricing wise hands down the best in town. \r\n\"CHICKEN CHOP KOMPOKKKK\" isn\'t my favorite but definitely the most ordered dish in this cafe. \r\n\r\nIf we are talking about the management just in our FCM faculty. It\'s a 50, 50. Mr Saddam do his job pretty well and clear things up when you are in doubt about the course. But some of the female staff (not pointing fingers, but I really have no idea about her name) can be a little challenging. She can sounds super annoyed by your enquiry/request, and feel so apathetic. (feels like, why are you bothering me? I\'m trying to chill here, can\'t you see i\'m tired?). If we are talking about the management of MMU in general. Everyone thinks they are shit, during my study, the SRC even brought it to the mainstream media about how shitty our MMU management really are. MONEY is their best interest, not the student\'s, not the lecturer\'s, that is why a lot of my lecturers cabut for good. \r\n\r\nAdditional point, the IDKWTF department near the in-campus hostel. For event purpose, I went to apply for permission for hanging banner, posters. They took my deposit and when the event is over, I want to get back my deposit. I visit the person in charge\'s office for so goddamn many times at different time. He\'s always missing in action. I have even waited there for hour. His colleague said he might be back in a while, but NEVER. In the end I gave up and just let them take the money. Later, jokes on me, my coursemate never bother to apply for permission and they didn\'t get any fine or any action taken. That says a lot about their work productivity.', 'Bachelor of Multimedia (Hons) Animation and Visual Effects', 2016, 34, 5, 2, 4, 5, 1, 1, '42.189.158.194'),
(481, '2021-09-21 19:14:08', 'Anonymous', 'sunlinetestphone@gmail.com', 'Tuition fee is much cheaper then others, can get offer by big company such as Google, Facebook and Huawei. Study hard to get good result, overall I never regret to choose this university.', 'Degree In software system development ', 2015, 78, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 1, '45.121.37.189'),
