(483, '2021-09-21 20:49:10', 'jenna', 'jennadellae@gmail.com', 'Completed my pre-u here as well, so technically I\'ve been here for 4 years. Overall, I am satisfied with it. It is famous for its environment and facilities, which I think did live up to its reputation. The lecturers are pretty a-ok. A mix of highly responsible, knowledgable, friendly, and helpful lecturers and extremely arrogant, rude, and disqualified individuals who I WOULD NOT consider as educators. Of course, it depends on your luck with choosing the course. Make sure to enrol after the pandemic if you want to experience a more well-versed uni life.', 'bachelor of psychology', 2018, 56, 4, 4, 3, 1, 4, 1, '175.144.73.187'),
(485, '2021-09-21 23:26:49', 'Amethyst20', 'vivianne_9722@hotmail.com', 'As a chef student,I can say that their facilities are really bad...10 mixers but only 3 can use,they did not upgrade anything at all.Even the pots and bowls are not enough.The management said they spend around millions Ringgit to renovate/upgrade the whole kitchen is bullshit.The aircond is not cool enough and the water pipe keeps leaking even though they said it already been â€œrepairedâ€.Spend 50k for the diploma course for all of this is not worth it. They are truely vampires,students are having class at home for months but still need to pay for the laboratory and resource fees, I really donâ€™t have any good comments for this college except the lecturers,they are really knowledgeable and they will answers all of the questions clearly when asking them.', 'Diploma in Professional Chef Training', 2019, 87, 1, 3, 4, 4, 1, 1, '161.142.187.24'),
(486, '2021-09-21 23:32:09', 'Annaaaa', 'yamamilan@gmail.com', 'If you would like to have a wonderful campus life, this campus definitely can fulfill your needs. And, this is also one of the reasons why I had chosen to take my diploma and degree with TarUC. It is also considered as a more affordable Uni in KL among the others. Just a little weak point, the degree of accounting/commerce are still not being recognized by MIA. But, overall the lecturers and tutors for business faculty are quite knowledgeable and experienced. Foods and hygiene could be better. Conclusion, I will rate my life with this campus 3.8 out of 5. ', 'Bachelor of Commerce ', 2014, 78, 4, 4, 3, 3, 3, 1, '115.135.215.2'),
(487, '2021-09-21 23:32:12', 'Mr Ms', 'jiaenhees0@gmail.com', 'Overall is okay, most lecturers are experienced, knowlegable, responsible and friendly. Coursework is quite heavy but still can survive. Tuition fee is affordable as compared to other private universities. The environment in KL campus is good and suitable for students. ', 'Bachelor of Social Science in Psychology', 2021, 78, 3, 4, 4, 4, 3, 1, '14.192.217.94'),
