(501, '2021-09-22 17:10:20', 'Student', 'hykxingelf@gmail.com', 'I was studying FIS and I agree that most of the FIS lecturers are quite professional, productive, ready to help, care about students and their teaching is understandable. \r\nFor MBBS, many good lecturers were leaving due to some \"workers\' benefits\" issues. FIS lecturers are actually more high quality than MBBS. Students pay more money to get low grade teaching.\r\nThe hostel is expensive yet like a 5 star jail.\r\nFor the transportation, Grab car is a better choice if you are rushing.', 'FIS, MBBS', 2020, 64, 5, 4, 3, 3, 3, 1, '113.211.130.97'),
(504, '2021-09-22 21:32:30', 'handsome', '99@gmail.com', 'FTSM does not have any strict rules. Just wear t-shirt, long pants and slippers to class is not a problem. Most of the lecturers are very kind and will answer all the questions. Taught in BM and BI (In general university, what do you expect teach in BI only??) But notes all are in English. Only FYP have to be done in BM. Food in FTSM is super duper expensive!!!! and the cost is actually determine from the pakcik means today cost rm1, tomorrow maybe rm1.50!!! So prepare some biscuit before getting to lecture class.', 'Computer Science', 2019, 47, 5, 4, 5, 2, 5, 1, '60.48.196.158'),
(505, '2021-09-22 22:28:59', 'Sui Sheng Yeng', 'soo@gmail.com', 'Overall great uni if you hope to join computing field. Lecturers are very responsible and eager to guide the students.', 'Bachelor Degree in Software Engineering', 2019, 41, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 1, '210.186.56.250'),
(506, '2021-09-22 23:02:22', 'peninsula warrior', 'xnivx01@outlook.com', 'Facilities are probably the best among local private unis around this price range. Of course, it has the upper hand regarding the location since it\'s Sunway City and Subang. The students are not as bad as what we heard in the rumours. However, lectures are very poor overall. As a year 2 undergraduate, the qualities of lectures and lecturers are far off compared to during foundation. Food is okay, quite boring compared to other unis. Management is good in some aspects but they refuse to acknowledge and IGNORE you in a very indirect way when they are at fault so be careful about that.', 'BIS (Hons) (Data Analytics)', 2023, 57, 5, 5, 2, 3, 3, 1, '42.189.194.165'),
(507, '2021-09-23 00:57:32', 'Blondie', 'janesatriana@gmail.com', 'THERE ARE BETTER UNIVERSITY OUT THERE. \r\nHELP should not be your only choice. \r\nThe management is awful, they won\'t help you at all, which is ironic with the name lol', 'Early Childhood Education', 2019, 40, 3, 3, 2, 2, 1, 1, '124.82.91.91');
INSERT INTO `schools` (`school_id`, `school_name`, `school_title`, `school_state`, `state_id`, `year_established`, `private/public`, `Description`, `Address`) VALUES
(1, 'Universiti Tunku Abdul Rahman (UTAR)', 'UTAR', 'Selangor', 100014, 2002, 'Private', 'A non-profit private research university in Malaysia. It is ranked top 100 in the Times Higher Education Asia University Rankings 2018 and top 600 in the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2021, placing it overall 2nd in Malaysia only after the University of Malaya.', 'Sungai Long, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(2, 'Universiti Tunku Abdul Rahman (UTAR)', 'UTARP', 'Perak', 100016, 2002, 'Private', 'A non-profit private research university in Malaysia. It is ranked top 100 in the Times Higher Education Asia University Rankings 2018 and top 600 in the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2021, placing it overall 2nd in Malaysia only after the University of Malaya.', 'Kampar, Perak, Malaysia'),
(3, 'Universiti Malaya', 'UM', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 1905, 'Public', 'The University of Malaya (UM) (Malay: Universiti Malaya) is a public research university located in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. It is the oldest and highest ranking Malaysian institution of higher education', 'Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia'),
(4, 'Universiti Teknologi Malaysia (UTM)', 'UTM', 'Johor', 10001, 1972, 'Public', 'University of Technology Malaysia (UTM) (Malay: Universiti Teknologi Malaysia) is a premier Malaysian public research-intensive university ranked 187th in the world by QS University rankings. Its medium of instruction is English.', 'Skudai, Iskandar Puteri, Johor, Malaysia'),
(5, 'Universiti Tun Hussein Onn Malaysia (UTHM)', 'UTHM', 'Johor', 10001, 1993, 'Public', 'Universiti Tun Hussein Onn Malaysia (UTHM; English: Tun Hussein Onn University of Malaysia) is a public university in Johor, Malaysia. It was formerly known as Institut Teknologi Tun Hussein Onn (ITTHO) and Kolej Universiti Teknologi Tun Hussein Onn (KUiTTHO).', 'Batu Pahat, Johor, Malaysia'),
(6, 'Raffles University Iskandar (RUI)', 'RUI', 'Johor', 10001, 2011, 'Private', 'A university established by Raffles Iskandar Sdn. Bhd.The University was formally approved by Malaysiaâ€™s Ministry of Higher Education (MOHE) on 31st October 2011.\r\n\r\n', 'Jalan Trus, Bandar Johor Bahru, Johor'),
(7, 'Universiti Utara Malaysia (UUM)', 'UUM', 'Kedah', 10002, 1984, 'Public', 'Universiti Utara Malaysia (UUM) was established on 16 February 1984 under the Universiti Utara Malaysia 1984 Order.It is known as a management university. UUM was ranked in the bracket of 591â€“600 in the QS World University Rankings 2020.', 'Sintok, Kedah, Malaysia'),
(8, 'AIMST University', 'AIMST', 'Kedah', 10002, 2001, 'Private', 'Asian Institute of Medicine, Science and Technology (AIMST University) is a profit private university in Malaysia. The university was built by Malaysian Indian Congress (MIC) to provide tertiary education, particularly to Malaysian Indian students in the medical, science and engineering fields and business management.', 'Bedong-Semeling, Sungai Petani, Kedah, Malaysia'),
(9, 'Albukhary International University', 'Albukhary', 'Kedah', 10002, 2010, 'Private', 'Albukhary International University (AIU) is a private nonprofit educational institution. It provides a learning environment for self-discovery, nurturing relationships, and building an understanding of global issues.', 'Bandar Alor Setar, Alor Setar, Kedah'),
(10, 'Universiti Islam Antarabangsa Sultan Abdul Halim M', 'UniSAHM', 'Kedah', 10002, 1995, 'Private', 'Sultan Abdul Halim Mu\'adzam Shah International Islamic University (UniSHAMS) is a private university operating from new official campus in Kedah. It was formerly known as Institiut Agama Islam Negeri Kedah\r\nKolej Universiti Insaniah', 'Kuala Ketil, Kedah, Malaysia'),
(11, 'Universiti Malaysia Kelantan (UMK)', 'UMK', 'Kelantan', 10003, 2007, 'Public', 'The Universiti Malaysia Kelantan (UMK; English: University of Malaysia, Kelantan) is a public university in Kelantan, Malaysia. Taglines such as â€œEntrepreneurship is Our Thrustâ€ and â€œEntrepreneurial Universityâ€ are used to promote the philosophy of the university.', 'Bachok (main), Pengkalan Chepa, Jeli, Kelantan, Malaysia'),
(12, 'Universiti Teknikal Malaysia Melaka (UTeM)', 'UTeM', 'Melaka', 10006, 2000, 'Public', 'Universiti Teknikal Malaysia Melaka (Technical University of Malaysia of Malacca) is a public university. It is the pioneer in the use of the \"Practice and Application Oriented\" teaching and learning method for tertiary level technical education in Malaysia.', 'Hang Tuah Jaya, Durian Tunggal, Malacca, Malaysia'),
(13, 'Universiti Sains Islam Malaysia (USIM)', 'USIM', 'Negeri Sembilan', 10007, 1998, 'Public', 'Universiti Sains Islam Malaysia (USIM) is an emerging Islamic university which is fully owned and funded by the Malaysian Government. Being the 12th Public Institution of Higher learning, it aims to spearhead knowledge and be the global reference centre for Islamic Science.', 'Nilai, Negeri Sembilan, Malaysia'),
(14, 'INTI International University Nilai (IIU)', 'IIU', 'Negeri Sembilan', 10007, 1986, 'Private', 'INTI International University & Colleges are private university colleges located in Malaysia. The main campus was initially known as INTI University College until 31 May 2010 when the Higher Education Ministry announced its upgrade to university status. It is owned by INTI Education Group which has formalised its partnership with Laureate International Universities in 2008.', 'Nilai'),
(15, 'Nilai University', 'Nilai', 'Negeri Sembilan', 10007, 1997, 'Private', 'Nilai University (Nilai U) received full \'university\' status and is a private university. The medium of instruction is English. Nilai U has three faculties offering diploma, bachelor\'s degree, master\'s degree and PhD programmes.', 'Nilai, Negeri Sembilan, Malaysia'),
(16, 'Manipal International University', 'MIU', 'Negeri Sembilan', 10007, 2011, 'Private', 'Manipal International University (MIU), is a Malaysian university offering multidisciplinary programs with a focus in the fields of science, engineering and management & business. It is a member of the Manipal Global Education Group. ', 'Putra Nilai, Negeri Sembilan, Malaysia'),
(17, 'Universiti Malaysia Pahang (UMP)', 'UMP', 'Pahang', 10008, 2002, 'Public', 'Universiti Malaysia Pahang (UMP) (English: University of Malaysia, Pahang) is a public technical university. It was formerly known as Kolej Universiti Kejuruteraan dan Teknologi Malaysia.', 'Pekan, Pahang, Malaysia'),
(18, 'DRB-HICOM University of Automotive Malaysia', 'DRB-HICOM', 'Pahang', 10008, 2010, 'Private', 'Began as International College of Automotive (ICAM) in April 2010, DRB-HICOM University of Automotive Malaysia became a full-fledged university in October 2015. Currently the university offers 25 programmes from foundation, diploma, degree and post-graduate studies with emphasize on the automotive eco-system.', 'Peramu Jaya Industrial Area, Pekan, Pahang'),
(20, 'Universiti Sains Malaysia (USM)', 'USM', 'Penang', 10009, 1969, 'Public', 'Universiti Sains Malaysia (abbreviated as USM) is a public research university. USM is the only Accelerated Programs for Excellence (APEX) government-funded autonomous university in Malaysia.', 'Penang, Malaysia'),
(21, 'Wawasan Open University', 'Wawasan', 'Penang', 10009, 2006, 'Private', 'Wawasan Open University, abbreviated as WOU, is a private university located in Penang, Malaysia that provides working adults with access to higher education via open distance learning (ODL). In September 2013, WOU began to also offer full-time degree programmes to STPM school leavers and diploma holders', 'Georgetown, Penang, Malaysia'),
(22, 'Universiti Pendidikan Sultan Idris (UPSI)', 'UPSI', 'Perak', 100016, 1922, 'Public', 'Sultan Idris Education University (Malay: Universiti Pendidikan Sultan Idris; commonly abbreviated as UPSI;) is a public university. First established in 1922 as a teachers college, it is one of the oldest functioning institutions of higher learning in Malaysia.', '	Tanjung Malim, Perak, Malaysia'),
(23, 'Quest International University Perak', 'Quest', 'Perak', 100016, 2011, 'Private', 'Quest International University Perak (QIUP) is a private and research institution that was first established under the Higher Educational Institutions Act 555 and is currently under the ownership of Global Integrated Training Associates Sdn Bhd.', 'Jalan Raja Permaisuri Bainun, Taman Chateau, Ipoh, Perak'),
(24, 'Universiti Sultan Azlan Shan', 'USAS', 'Perak', 100016, 1999, 'Private', 'Sultan Azlan Shah University (Malay: Universiti Sultan Azlan Shah) (USAS) is a private university in Malaysia. It was previously known as Sultan Azlan Shah Islamic University College (KUISAS).', 'Kuala Kangsar, Perak, Malaysia'),
(25, 'Universiti Malaysia Perlis (UniMAP)', 'UniMAP', 'Perlis', 100010, 2001, 'Public', 'Universiti Malaysia Perlis (UniMAP) is a Malaysian public institution of higher learning located in Perlis. It was previously known as Kolej Universiti Kejuruteraan Utara Malaysia (English: Northern Malaysia University College of Engineering).', 'Kangar and Arau, Perlis, Malaysia'),
(26, 'Limkokwing University of Creative Technology', 'LKW', 'Putrajaya', 100011, 1991, 'Private', 'Limkokwing University of Creative Technology (also referred to as Limkokwing and LUCT) is a private international university that has a presence across Africa, Europe, and Asia. With its main campus in Malaysia, the university has over 30,000 students from more than 150 countries.', 'Cyberjaya, Kuala Lumpur, Kuching, Malacca, Beijing, Gaborone, London, Maseru, Mbabane, Phnom Penh, Sierra Leone, Namataba.'),
(27, 'University Malaysia of Computer Science and Engine', 'UMoCSE', 'Putrajaya', 100011, 2012, 'Private', 'University Malaysia of Computer Science and Engineering (UNIMY), is a wholly owned subsidiary of Serba Dinamik Group Berhad is an ICT private university that was established in the year 2012 with the motto â€” Future Begins @ UNIMY, signifying the application of fast advancing technological innovation for the benefit of humanity. ', 'Block 12, Star Central, Lingkaran Cyber Point Timur, 63000 Cyberjaya, Selangor'),
(28, 'Universiti Tenaga Nasional (UNITEN)', 'UNITEN', 'Putrajaya', 100011, 1999, 'Private', 'Universiti Tenaga Nasional (UNITEN) is a private university, located in Selangor, Malaysia, with GLC university status. It is wholly owned by the public-listed Tenaga Nasional Berhad (TNB),', 'Kajang, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(29, 'Universiti Malaysia Sabah (UMS)', 'UMS', 'Sabah', 100012, 1994, 'Public', 'Universiti Malaysia Sabah (UMS) is a public university in Malaysia. The university is located on a 999-acre site at Sepanggar Bay in Kota Kinabalu in the Malaysian state of Sabah. With Mount Kinabalu and the South China Sea as its background, UMS is often considered as among the most beautiful campuses in Southeast Asia.', 'Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia'),
(30, 'Universiti Malaysia Sarawak (UNIMAS)', 'UNIMAS', 'Sarawak', 100013, 1992, 'Public', 'Universiti Malaysia Sarawak (UNIMAS; English: University of Malaysia, Sarawak) is a Malaysian public university. UNIMAS was officially incorporated on 24 December 1992. Recently, UNIMAS has been ranked among top 200th in Asian University Rankings 2017 by QS World University Rankings.', 'Kota Samarahan, Sarawak, Malaysia'),
(31, 'Universiti Malaysia Terengganu (UMT)', 'UMT', 'Terengganu', 100015, 1979, 'Public', 'The Universiti Malaysia Terengganu (University of Malaysia, Terengganu) or UMT, formerly known as Kolej Universiti Sains dan Teknologi Malaysia (University College of Science and Technology Malaysia) or KUSTEM. It was officially chartered on 1 February 2007.', 'Kuala Nerus, Terengganu, Malaysia'),
(32, 'Sultan Zainal Abidin (UniSZA)', 'UniSZA', 'Terengganu', 100015, 2005, 'Public', 'Universiti Sultan Zainal Abidin (abbreviated as UniSZA)  is the 18th public institution of higher learning. The university is a creature of the Act of Parliament known as the Universities and University Colleges Act 1971, with its constitution laid down under the Universities and University Colleges (Variation of, and Addition to, the Constitution)(Universiti Sultan Zainal Abidin) Order 2010.', 'Kuala Terengganu (Gong Badak [Main Campus] and Kota)'),
(33, 'Universiti Kuala Lumpur (UniKL)', 'UniKL', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 2002, 'Private', 'Universiti Kuala Lumpur (UniKL) is a multi-campus technical university with its main campus based in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. Rated as a Tier-5 \"Excellent University\" by the Ministry of Higher Education Malaysia in 2009, 2011, and 2013 UniKL has 14 institutes spread across 12 campuses throughout Malaysia', 'Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia'),
(34, 'Multimedia University (MMU), Cyberjaya', 'MMU', 'Selangor', 100014, 1996, 'Private', 'Multimedia University, abbreviated as MMU, is the first ever full-fledged private research undergraduate-focused university in Malaysia and a government-linked university as it is owned by Telekom Malaysia. Formerly known as nstitute of Telecommunication and Information Technology (1994-1996) and Telekom University (UniTELE) (1996-1999).', 'Ayer Keroh, Cyberjaya'),
(35, 'Universiti Pertahanan Nasional Malaysia, (UPNM)', 'UPNM', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 1995, 'Public', 'The National Defence University of Malaysia (UPNM; Malay: Universiti Pertahanan Nasional Malaysia) is a military university located in Sungai Besi Camp, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.\r\n\r\nThe university is Malaysia\'s first catering to the needs and development of the Malaysian Armed Forces.', 'Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia'),
(36, 'International Medical University (IMU)', 'IMU', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 1992, 'Private', 'The International Medical University (IMU) is a private, English language, health sciences university in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, and Malaysia\'s leading private medical and healthcare university. It was established in 1992, and is active in research and teaching within medicine and healthcare with a strong international orientation.', 'Bukit Jalil, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia'),
(37, 'Open University Malaysia (OUM)', 'OUM', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 2000, 'Private', 'Open University Malaysia, abbreviated as OUM, is the 7th Malaysian private university and it is owned by the Multimedia Technology Enhancement Operations (METEOR) Sdn. Bhd, a consortium of 11 Malaysian public universities. It leverages on the quality, prestig', 'Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia'),
(38, 'International Centre for Education in Islamic Finance', 'INCEIF', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 2006, 'Private', 'INCEIF (International Centre for Education in Islamic Finance) was set up by Bank Negara Malaysia (Central Bank of Malaysia) in 2005 to develop human capital for the global Islamic finance industry. Commonly known as INCEIF â€“ The Global University of Islamic Finance, it is the only university in the world dedicated to Islamic finance.', 'Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia'),
(39, 'Asia e University (AeU)', 'AeU', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 2007, 'Private', 'Asia e University (AeU) is an international university in Subang Jaya, Malaysia that offers on-campus, blended and online learning mode programmes. An institution set in Asia, by Asians, and for Asia â€“ founded by the Asia Cooperation Dialogue foreign ministers', ''),
(40, 'HELP University KL', 'HELPKL', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 1986, 'Private', 'HELP University (Malay: Universiti HELP; formerly known as HELP Institute, and subsequently as HELP University College) is a private university in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. HELP Institute was awarded the University College status in 2004 by the Ministry of Higher Education, Malaysia.[1] In 2011, it was awarded full university status.', '	ELM Business School, No. 15, Jalan Sri Semantan 1, Off Jalan Semantan, Bukit Damansara, 50490, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia'),
(41, 'Asia Pacific University of Technology and Innovation (APU)', 'APU', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 1993, 'Private', 'The Asia Pacific University of Technology and Innovation (colloquially known as APU) is a private university in Malaysia. It was formed in 1993 as the Asia Pacific Institute of Information Technology (APIIT) and was renamed in 2004 after being granted University College status to Asia Pacific University College of Technology and Innovation (UCTI).', 'Jalan Teknologi 5, Taman Teknologi Malaysia, 57000 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur'),
(43, 'International University of Malaya-Wales', 'IUMW', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 2012, 'Private', 'International University of Malaya-Wales (IUMW) is an international joint university based in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. It was founded in 2012 as a partnership between the University of Malaya (UM) and the University of Wales Trinity Saint David (UWTSD).\r\n\r\n', 'City Campus, Ground Floor, Block A, Administration Wing, Jalan Tun Ismail, 50480 Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lumpur'),
(44, 'Asia School of Business', 'ASB', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 2015, 'Private', 'Asia School of Business (ASB) is a partnership between MIT Sloan School of Management and Bank Negara Malaysia (the Central Bank of Malaysia). The partnership is a business school offering business administration related courses in the form of a 20-month full-time MBA program and executive education classes for students from Malaysia and around the world.', 'Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia'),
(45, 'Meritus University', 'Meritus', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 2016, 'Private', 'As a niche university, MERITUSâ€™s unique approach to education is to offer a practical and effective blend of traditional, modern and experiential learning to ensure success. Unlike other universities which only focuses on the academia, MERITUS is committed to producing well rounded graduates, capable of meeting the demands of todayâ€™s employers, instilled with the virtues of success and are sought after by top organisations upon graduation.', 'Mid Valley Megamall, 49, Lingkaran Syed Putra, Mid Valley City, 59200 Kuala Lumpur'),
(46, 'UCSI University', 'UCSI', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 1986, 'Private', 'UCSI University is a comprehensive university in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. UCSI offers various disciplines, which include medicine, pharmacy, engineering, IT, applied sciences, business, architecture, music, social sciences, creative arts and hospitality, at undergraduate and postgraduate levels.', 'Taman Connaught, Cheras, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia'),
(47, 'Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia (UKM)', 'UKM', 'Selangor', 100014, 1970, 'Public', 'The National University of Malaysia (Malay: Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia), abbreviated as UKM, is a public university. National University of Malaysia is one of six research universities in the country. It was ranked number 259th in the world by QS World University Rankings in 2014.', 'Bandar Baru Bangi, Selangor, Malaysia.'),
(48, 'Universiti Putra Malaysia (UPM)', 'UPM', 'Selangor', 100014, 1931, 'Public', 'Universiti Putra Malaysia (UPM; formerly known as Universiti Pertanian Malaysia or College of Agriculture Malaya or School of Agriculture) is recognised by the independent government assessments as one of Malaysia\'s leading research universities offering undergraduate and postgraduate courses with a focus on agricultural sciences and its related fields.', '	Serdang, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(49, 'Universiti Teknologi MARA (UiTM)', 'UiTM', 'Selangor', 100014, 1956, 'Public', 'Universiti Teknologi MARA (UiTM) is a public university based primarily in Shah Alam, Malaysia, that accepts only bumiputera. It was established to help rural Malays in 1956 as the RIDA (Rural & Industrial Development Authority) Training Centre (Malay: Dewan Latihan RIDA), and opened with around 50 students.', 'Shah Alam, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(50, 'Universiti Islam Antarabangsa Malaysia (UIAM)', 'UIAM', 'Selangor', 100014, 1983, 'Public', 'The International Islamic University Malaysia (Malay: Universiti Islam Antarabangsa Malaysia)  also known as IIUM, is a public university in Malaysia. The university is sponsored by eight governments and the Organisation of the Islamic Cooperation (OIC).', 'Gombak, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(51, 'Universiti Tun Abdul Razak (UniRAZAK)', 'UniRAZAK', 'Selangor', 100014, 1997, 'Private', 'Universiti Tun Abdul Razak (UNIRAZAK)[1] was established on 18 December 1997 and is one of the earliest private universities in Malaysia. UNIRAZAK was wholly acquired by Yayasan Pelaburan Bumiputera, the foundation that owns the national investment management fund Permodalan Nasional Berhad (PNB).', 'Lot 195A, Jalan Tun Razak, 50400 Kuala Lumpur'),
(52, 'Universiti Teknologi Petronas (UTP)', 'UTP', 'Selangor', 100014, 1997, 'Private', 'Universiti Teknologi PETRONAS (UTP) is a Malaysian research university. It is wholly owned by Petroliam Nasional Berhad (PETRONAS), Malaysia\'s oil and gas multinational corporation. The university conducts research activities in collaboration with PETRONAS on six research areas.', 'Seri Iskandar, Perak, Malaysia'),
(53, 'Malaysia University of Science & Technology (MUST)', 'MUST', 'Selangor', 100014, 1997, 'Private', 'The Malaysia University of Science and Technology (MUST) was established in January 1997 when, then Prime Minister, Mahathir Mohamad and a delegation from Malaysia made a working visit to Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) and endorsed the establishment of a university modeled after MIT.', 'Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(54, 'Al-Madinah International University (MEDIU)', 'MEDIU', 'Selangor', 100014, 2006, 'Private', 'The Al-Madinah International University (MEDIU; Malay: Universiti Antarabangsa Al-Madinah) is an independent educational institution in Malaysia. It was established in 2006, founded on Islamic principles and values. The university aims for knowledge development and intellectual exchange consistent with international level of excellence.', 'Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory, Malaysia'),
(55, 'Management and Science University (MSU)', 'MSU', 'Selangor', 100014, 2001, 'Private', 'Management & Science University (abbreviated as MSU Malaysia or simply MSU) is a private university in Malaysia. The university was founded in 2001 as University College of Technology & Management Malaysia before officially became a full fledge university in October 2007 as Management & Science University', 'Shah Alam, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(56, 'Taylorâ€™s University', 'Taylors', 'Selangor', 100014, 2006, 'Private', 'Taylor\'s University (commonly referred to as Taylor\'s) is a private university in Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia. It is often regarded as Malaysia\'s top private university in Malaysia based on the QS World University Rankings. It was founded in 1969 as a college, was awarded university college status in 2006, and university status in 2010.', 'Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(57, 'Sunway University', 'Sunway', 'Selangor', 100014, 2004, 'Private', 'Sunway University is a private university in Bandar Sunway, Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia. It offers undergraduate and postgraduate programmes taught in English.', '	Bandar Sunway, Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(58, 'UNITAR International University', 'UNITAR', 'Selangor', 100014, 1997, 'Private', 'Established in 1997, UNITAR International University (UNITAR) is a visionary and well-governed institution, known for being the first virtual university in Southeast Asia and one of the pioneering private universities in Malaysia.', 'UNITAR International University Tierra Crest, Jalan SS 6/3, Ss 6, 47301 Petaling Jaya, Selangor'),
(59, 'Malaysia Institute of Supply Chain Innovation (MISI)', 'MISI', 'Selangor', 100014, 2011, 'Private', 'The Malaysia Institute for Supply Chain Innovation (MISI) is a supply chain post-graduate school located in Shah Alam, Malaysia. The school was launched as a joint initiative between the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) and the Government of Malaysia on March 22, 2011. MISI is a member of the MIT Global SCALE Network. MISI offers post-graduate and executive education programs in supply chain management.', 'Persiaran Tebar Layar, Bukit Jelutong, 40150 Shah Alam, Selangor'),
(60, 'Binary University of Management and Entrepreneurship', 'Binary', 'Selangor', 100014, 1984, 'Private', 'MALAYSIA Binary University is one of the most established and respected university for management, IT and entrepreneurship education in Asia. The University also places great emphasis on research and to this end has dedicated research centers in social entrepreneurship, women leadership, business entrepreneurship and advanced management.', 'Ioi Business Park, NO. 1, 47100 Puchong, Selangor'),
(61, 'SEGi University', 'SEGi', 'Selangor', 100014, 1977, 'Private', 'SEGi University and Colleges first opened its doors as Systematic College in 1977 in the heart of Kuala Lumpurâ€™s commercial district; offering globally recognised professional qualifications.', 'Kota Damansara, 47810 Petaling Jaya, Selangor'),
(62, 'Infrastructure University Kuala Lumpur (IUKL)', 'IUKL', 'Selangor', 100014, 1998, 'Private', 'The Infrastructure University Kuala Lumpur (IUKL; Malay: Universiti Infrastruktur Kuala Lumpur), formerly known as Kuala Lumpur Infrastructure University College (KLIUC), is a \r\nprivate university in Kajang, Selangor, Malaysia. It is the first infrastructure university in Malaysia. It was established in 1998 following the privatisation of the Research and Training Institute of Public Works Department of Malaysia (IKRAM).', 'Unipark Suria, Jalan Ikram-Uniten, 43000 Kajang, Selangor'),
(63, 'Putra Business School', 'Putra', 'Selangor', 100014, 2011, 'Public', 'Putra Business School (PBS) was formerly known as the Graduate School of Management (GSM), Universiti Putra Malaysia (UPM). It is a leading business school in Malaysia and the first post-graduate business school accreditated by AACSB - The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business. Less than 5% of business schools worldwide have these accreditation.', 'Putra Business School, Level 3, Office Building of the Deputy Vice Chancellor (Research & Innovation) 43400, UPM, 43400 Seri Kembangan, Selangor'),
(64, 'MAHSA University', 'MAHSA', 'Selangor', 100014, 2005, 'Private', 'Mahsa University is a private medical university in Jenjarom, Selangor. It was founded in Pusat Bandar Damansara in 2005 as a college, and was upgraded to university status in 2009ã€‚', 'Jln SP 2, Bandar Saujana Putra, 42610 Jenjarom, Selangor'),
(65, 'Universiti Islam Malaysia, Cyberjaya', 'UIMC', 'Selangor', 100014, 1963, 'Private', 'Universiti Islam Malaysia (Islamic University of Malaysia) - or UIM in short - is the first and only postgraduate-only university in Malaysia. The administration and academic offices are located in Cyberjaya with its permanent campus currently under development.', 'Bangunan Khadijah, PT1, Jln Profesor Diraja Ungku Aziz, 46350 Petaling Jaya, Selangor'),
(66, 'City University', 'CityU', 'Selangor', 100014, 1984, 'Private', 'City University is a private university in Selangor, Malaysia. It was founded in April 1984 by a group of scholars in local public and overseas universities.', 'No.8, Jalan 223/51A, Selangor, Seksyen 51a, 46100 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(67, 'Universiti Selangor (UNISEL)', 'UNISEL', 'Selangor', 100014, 1999, 'Private', 'The University of Selangor (abbreviation: UNISEL) is a private university in Selangor, Malaysia, wholly owned and managed by the Selangor state government independently â€” without funding from the Malaysian federal government (and is thus regarded as a \"private\" as opposed to a \"public\" university).', 'Bestari Jaya (Batang Berjuntai), Shah Alam, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(68, 'Asia Metropolitan University', 'AMU', 'Selangor', 100014, 2004, 'Private', 'AMU is a well-established higher education institute offering a wide range of programmes from undergraduate to post-graduate levels. Their programmes are fully accredited by MQA. The University is internationally recognized by the Accreditation Service for International Colleges (ASIC) and is also a full-member of the Association of Commonwealth Universities.', 'Taman Kemacahaya, 43200 Cheras, Selangor'),
(69, 'International University College of Technology Twintech (IUCTT)', 'IUCTT', 'Sabah', 100012, 1993, 'Private', 'The Twintech International University College of Technology, or Twintech for short, is a private publicly funded university college in Malaysia. Twintech International University College of Technology, formerly known as L&G-Twintech Institute of Technology, is a private institution of higher learning licensed by the Ministry of Education. The university college is owned and managed by Twintech Holding Sdn. Bhd.', '	Bandar Sri Damansara, Petaling, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(70, 'Southern University College', 'SUC', 'Johor', 10001, 1990, 'Private', 'Southern University College, abbreviated as Southern UC, is a non-profit, private university college in Malaysia. It is the first non-profit higher education institute and private university college in Skudai, Johor.\r\n\r\nCurrently, Southern UC have 7 faculties, 3 schools, 6 research institutes and 7 academic centres.', ' PTD 64888, Jalan Selatan Utama km 15, Taman Perusahaan Ringan Pulai, 81300 Skudai, Johor'),
(71, 'Islamic University College of Science & Technology', 'IUCST', 'Kelantan', 10003, 2005, '', '', NULL),
(72, 'Kuala Lumpur Metropolitan University College (KLMUC)', 'KLMUC', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 1991, 'Private', 'Kuala Lumpur Metropolitan University College (KLMUC, Malay: Kolej Universiti Metropolitan Kuala Lumpur) is a university college located in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. It was established in 1991. The College currently offers over 17 programmes in 3 distinctive faculties.', 'Level G, 1-3 Wisma Sachdev, Jln Raja Laut, 50350 Kuala Lumpur'),
(73, 'Berjaya University College of Hospitality', 'Berjaya', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 2008, 'Private', 'Berjaya University College (formerly known as Berjaya University College of Hospitality) is a private university college in Malaysia, located within Berjaya Times Square, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. Berjaya UC offers qualifications in business, culinary arts, hospitality and tourism higher education, as well as liberal arts, from foundation to postgraduate levels.', 'Berjaya Times Square, No 1, Jalan Imbi, 55100 Kuala Lumpur'),
(74, 'Geomatika University College', 'Geomatika', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 2000, 'Private', '\r\nGeomatika University College (GUC) started as a Vocational Centre in 2000, carving a niche in Land Surveying. Noting a growing demand for such a specialisation, Geomatika submitted an application for college status and obtained the approval from the Ministry of Education.', 'Taman Setiawangsa, 54200, Kuala Lumpur, WP Kuala Lumpur'),
(75, 'Kolej Universiti Poly-Tech MARA', 'KUPTM', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 0, 'Private', 'Can\'t find it', 'Taman Shamelin Perkasa, 56100 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur'),
(76, 'PICOMS International University College', 'PICOMS', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 0, 'Private', 'Too lazy too find this, email me if u got it.', 'Taman Batu Muda Batu Caves, 68100 Kuala Lumpur'),
(78, 'Tunku Abdul Rahman University College', 'TARUC', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 1969, 'Private', 'Tunku Abdul Rahman University College, abbreviated TAR UC, is a non-profit, private university college in Malaysia. Named after the country\'s first prime minister, Tunku Abdul Rahman, the school was founded in 1969 as Tunku Abdul Rahman College (or TAR College) by the Malaysian Chinese Association (MCA). On 2 May 2013, it officially became a university college.', 'Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia'),
(79, 'Melaka Islamic University College', 'MIUC', 'Melaka', 10006, 1996, 'Private', 'The Islamic University College of Melaka or known as KUIM is a higher education institution owned by the state of Melaka which is formed in 1996. KUIM was upgraded to a university college in 2009 by the Ministry of Higher Education of Malaysia. Formerly known as the International Islamic Technology College of Melaka (KTIAM), the university college implements a new way of education through the combination of Islamic studies, science and the discipline of psychology.', 'KM 25, 78200 Kuala Sungai Baru, Melaka'),
(80, 'Kolej Universiti Agrosains Malaysia', 'KUAM', 'Melaka', 10006, 1999, 'Private', 'University College of Agroscience Malaysia or UCAM ; formerly known as Kolej RISDA is an IPTS established on 08 January 1999 under the Private Higher Education Institutions Act 1996. UCAM is a RISDA Owned Company under the Ministry of Development Rural (KPLB). The proto form of RISDA College is the RISDA Training Institute, which has been upgraded to RISDA College.', '2020, Ayer Pa\'abas, 78000 Alor Gajah, Melaka'),
(81, 'Linton University College', 'Linton', 'Negeri Sembilan', 10007, 1985, 'Private', 'The Linton University College was formerly known as Linton College and was founded in 1985 in Ipoh, Perak. In its early stages, the college concentrated on offering vocational and diploma level programmes in engineering, namely Electrical & Electronic, Mechanical, Mechatronic, Civil and Building engineering. Since 1993, Kolej Linton has been conducting Higher National Diploma (HND) courses in collaborative understanding with Nottingham Trent University (TNTU).', 'Bandar Universiti Teknologi Legenda (BUTL), Batu 12, 71700 Mantin, Negeri Sembilan'),
(82, 'KPJ Healthcare University College', 'KPJ', 'Negeri Sembilan', 10007, 1991, 'Private', 'KPJ Healthcare University College (KPJUC) (formerly known as PNC International College of Nursing and Health Sciences) is a subsidiary of KPJ Healthcare Berhad, a key private healthcare services provider. Established on 1st April 1991, KPJUC has been right from the outset, a progressive and entrepreneurial institution of higher learning with an international vision, placing students at the core of the heart of everything it does.', 'Lot PT 17010, Persiaran Seriemas Utama, Kota Seriemas, 71800 Nilai, Negeri Sembilan'),
(84, 'Kolej Universiti Islam Pahang Sultan Ahmad Shah', 'KUIPSAS', 'Pahang', 10008, 1996, 'Private', 'The existence of the Pahang Sultan Ahmad Shah Islamic University College (KUIPSAS) formerly known as the Pahang Sultan Ahmad Shah Islamic College (KIPSAS) is the first starting point towards the development and progress of Islamic higher education in the state. Its history began on 27 August 1996 when the Pahang State Executive Council approved the idea of â€‹â€‹its establishment.', 'KM 8 Jalan Gambang, 25150 Kuantan, Pahang\r\n'),
(85, 'University College of Yayasan Pahang', 'UCYP', 'Pahang', 10008, 0, 'Private', 'Took me too long to search, so imma leave it like this. :)', 'University College of Yayasan Pahang 2nd Floor, Kompleks Yayasan Pahang, Jalan Tanjung Lumpur, 26060 Kuantan, Pahang'),
(86, 'Vinayaka Mission International University College', 'Vinayka', 'Penang', 10009, 0, 'Private', 'Took me too long to search, so imma leave it like this. :)', 'Kampus Pulau Pinang, Aras 6, Menara NB 1,\r\nNo. 5050, Jalan Bagan Luar,\r\n12000 Butterworth\r\nMalaysia'),
(87, 'KDU University College', 'KDUpenang', 'Penang', 10009, 1983, 'Private', 'KDU Penang University College is a member of Paramount Education, a fully integrated provider that offers quality education from primary and secondary, both local and international, through to undergraduate and post-graduate levels, as well as executive and professional development programmes.', '32, Jalan Anson, George Town, 10400 George Town, Pulau Pinang'),
(88, 'Han Chiang University College of Communication', 'HanChiang', 'Penang', 10009, 1999, 'Private', 'Han Chiang University College of Communication, abbreviated as Han Chiang UC, is a not-for-profit private university college. For 100 years, Han Chiang has been pioneering affordable yet quality education for the benefit of its community.', 'Jalan Lim Lean Teng, George Town, Penang, Malaysia'),
(90, 'North Borneo University College, Sabah', 'NBUC', 'Sabah', 100012, 1996, 'P', 'The North Borneo University College (NBUC) is the first private university established in State of Sabah. Established under Private Higher Educational Institutions Act 1996, recognised by Ministry of Education Malaysia and full member of The Association of Commonwealth Universities (ACU, UK). NBUC is a nationally accredited university with a distinguished historical name of North Borneo in acknowledgement to the history and diversity in ethnicity, culture and language for the State of Sabah.', 'Wisma Angkatan Hebat, One Borneo Mall, 88400 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah'),
(91, 'University College Sabah Foundation (UCSF)', 'UCSF', 'Sabah', 100012, NULL, 'Private', 'UCSF focus its primary development based on the strengths and opportunities of Sabah, thereby actively partnering in the development of the state. On the human talent development side its future-proof graduates will add value, beyond merely economic, not only to Sabah, but also the nation and the world at large.', '20, Jalan Sanzac, Taman Sempelang, 88100 Kota Kinabalu, Sabah'),
(93, 'University College of Technology Sarawak', 'UCTS', 'Sarawak', 100013, 2013, 'Private', 'University College of Technology Sarawak (UCTS) was established in 2013, and the soft-launching ceremony was made on 2014 by then Chief Minister of Sarawak, Pehin Sri Abdul Taib Mahmud. It is among the few universities in Malaysia to plan its own Technology Park.', 'Sibu, Malaysia'),
(94, 'Selangor International Islamic University College (SIUC)', 'SIUC', 'Selangor', 100014, 1995, 'Private', 'The Selangor International Islamic University College (Malay: \'Kolej Universiti Islam Antarabangsa Selangor\') also known as KUIS is a private university located in Bandar Seri Putra, Bangi, Selangor. The college moved to this location in 2000, when the new campus was officially opened by Sharafuddin of Selangor.', 'Bangi, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(95, 'University of Cyberjaya', 'UoC', 'Selangor', 100014, 2005, 'Private', 'University of Cyberjaya (UoC) is a registered and accredited[1] private university with a focus on healthcare programmes. Initially known as Cyberjaya University College of Medical Sciences (CUCMS).', 'Cyberjaya, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(96, 'UOW Malaysia KDU', 'UOWKDU', 'Selangor', 100014, 1983, 'Private', 'UOW Malaysia KDU (Formerly known as KDU University College) is a private university college in Malaysia, with its flagship campus in Utropolis Glenmarie, Shah Alam. Established in 1983, and a pioneer in Malaysian private education, UOW Malaysia KDU was one of the first private colleges in Malaysia to have its own purpose-built campus. KDU offers education programmes at the Certificate, Diploma, Degree and Masters levels.', 'Jalan Kontraktor U1/14, Seksyen U1, Glenpark U1, 40150 Shah Alam, Selangor'),
(97, 'Lincoln University College', 'Lincoln', 'Selangor', 100014, 2002, 'Private', 'Lincoln University College, Petaling Jaya, Malaysia, was founded in the year in 2002 as Lincoln College and in 2011 Lincoln College was upgraded to Lincoln University College. The University College has got 5 Star ranking by Ministry of Higher Education, Malaysia in 2017 and 2019. Lincoln University College among the nine Malaysian universities listed in the Times Higher Education (THE) University Impact Rankings 2019 ranked 80th in Quality Education provider in 2020 TIMES ranking .', 'Petaling Jaya, Selangor'),
(98, 'First City University College', 'FCUC', 'Selangor', 100014, 1990, 'Private', 'First City University College was previously known as Kolej Bandar Utama (KBU),[1] began operation in 1990. It is a private university college in Bandar Utama, Malaysia.', 'Petaling Jaya, Selangor'),
(99, 'New Era University College', 'NewEra', 'Selangor', 100014, 1997, 'Private', 'New Era University College also referred to by its acronym NEUC is a private, non-profit higher education institution. NEUC is a LCCI Registered Training Centres (RTC),[2] and also a Cisco Networking Academy, teaches students networking and other information technology-related courses such as CCNA (Cisco Certified Network Associate) and CCNP (Cisco Certified Network Professional).', 'Kajang, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(100, 'Fairview University College', 'Fairview', 'Selangor', 100014, 2015, 'Private', 'On the 18th July 2012, The Minister of Higher Education formally invited the Board of Directors of Fairview International School (FIS) to submit an application to establish a private higher education institution with university college status. This was based on Fairviewâ€™s experience and expertise in running the IB approach in teaching and learning in Malaysia.', 'Subang Jaya, Selangor'),
(101, 'Saito University College', 'Saito', 'Selangor', 100014, 1988, 'Private', 'Saito University College is an award-winning 30-year-old education institution founded by Mr. Tetsuo Saito with its roots deep in design-based courses but has over the past decade diversified into security, law enforcement, business, hospitality, culinary arts, logistics, education and languages programmes. Initially known as Saito Academy of Graphic Design â€“ Malaysiaâ€™s FIRST Diploma in Graphic Design programme.', 'SECTION 52, 18, Jalan Tengah, Pj New Town, 46200 Petaling Jaya, Selangor'),
(102, 'Genovasi University College', 'Genovasi', 'Selangor', 100014, 2012, 'Private', 'Genovasi Malaysia was launched on 1st August 2012 as a means to equip Malaysians with an innovation mindset using the Design Thinking (DT) methodology. Its initial implementation was aimed at enhancing public service delivery. Since then, its efforts have expanded to support the demand from the private sector who see the benefits of human-centred design strategies.', 'Lot 2A, (Gate C, Jalan 13/2, Seksyen 13, 46200 Petaling Jaya, Selangor'),
(103, 'TATI University College', 'TATI', 'Terengganu', 100015, 1993, 'Private', 'University College TATI (UC TATI), formerly known as TATI University College and Terengganu Advanced Technical Institute (TATI), is a private university college located in Kemaman, Terengganu, Malaysia', 'Kemaman, Terengganu, Malaysia'),
(104, 'Bestari University College', 'Bestari', 'Terengganu', 100015, 2012, 'Private', 'University College Bestari (UC Bestari) is the first University College that strives to provide higher education opportunities to the poor and orphaned children with diverse ethnic background throughout Malaysia. They are making significant contributions to the human capital development and knowledge towards a sustainable future of the nation.', 'Putera Jaya, Permaisuri, Setiu, Terengganu, Malaysia, 22100 Permaisuri, Terengganu'),
(105, 'Newcastle University Medicine Malaysia', 'Newcastle', 'Johor', 10001, 2009, 'Private', 'Newcastle University UK, established an international branch campus, Newcastle University Medicine Malaysia (NUMed) in Johor, Malaysia in 2011. The campus provides undergraduate degrees in Medicine (MB BS) and Biomedical Sciences (BSc), as well as opportunities for foundation and postgraduate study. The programmes of study are identical to Newcastleâ€™s UK-based provision, and lead to the award of the same degrees, conferred by Newcastle University, UK. ', '79200 Gelang Patah, Johor'),
(106, 'University of Southampton Malaysia Campus', 'Southampto', 'Johor', 10001, 2012, 'Private', 'The university is invited by the Ministry of Higher Education to establish a branch campus for engineering within the EduCity development in Iskandar, Malaysia with their campus opening in October 2012.', 'No. 3, Persiaran Canselor 1, Educity Kota Ilmu, 79200 Nusajaya, Johor'),
(107, 'University of Reading Malaysia', 'Reading', 'Johor', 10001, 2016, 'Private', 'The University of Reading Malaysia (UoRM) is the first overseas campus of the University of Reading in the UK and is based in EduCity, Iskandar Puteri. The campus was officially inaugurated in February 2016. Ranked in the top 200 of universities worldwide (QS World University Rankings 2019), the University has a long-established international reputation for the quality of its teaching and research.', 'Kota Ilmu, Persiaran Graduan, Educity, 79200 Nusajaya, Johor'),
(108, 'Royal College of Surgeons In Ireland And University College Dublin ', 'RCSI', 'Penang', 10009, 1996, 'Private', 'RCSI & UCD Malaysia Campus (Formerly known as Penang Medical College (PMC)) is a private medical university in Penang, Malaysia. It is one of the Foreign University Branch Campus in Malaysia, in collaboration with Royal College of Surgeons in Ireland and University College Dublin.', 'Georgetown, Penang, Malaysia'),
(109, 'Curtin University', 'Curtin', 'Sarawak', 100013, 1999, 'Private', 'Curtin University, Malaysia (Curtin Malaysia) is the largest international campus of Curtin University, a university based in Perth, Western Australia. It provides local and international students with higher education in Sarawak, Malaysia.', 'CDT 250, 98009 Miri, Sarawak'),
(110, 'Swinburne University of Technology', 'Swinburne', 'Sarawak', 100013, 2000, 'Private', 'Swinburne University of Technology Sarawak Campus is the foreign branch campus of Swinburne University. Swinburne Sarawak operates as a partnership between the Sarawak State Government and Swinburne Australia. The initiative behind the Sarawak campus is part of a long term strategy by Swinburne Australia to \"globalize its operations and provide its students with international living, working and learning opportunities\".', 'Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia'),
(111, 'Heriot-Watt University Malaysia', 'Heriot-Wat', 'Putrajaya', 100011, 2015, 'Private', 'Heriot-Watt University Malaysiaâ€™s purpose-built campus opened to students in Putrajaya in September 2014 and the formal launch took place on 12 February 2015. The Â£35m campus sits on 4.8 acres in a stunning lakeside location providing exceptional educational facilities in an excellent environment, close to the Putrajaya marina and its modern leisure and sports facilities. This is a fantastic green area, part of Putrajaya Lakeâ€™s â€˜green continuumâ€™, and the building design is a conscious reference.', '1, Jalan Venna P5/2, Precinct 5, 62200 Putrajaya, Wilayah Persekutuan Putrajaya'),
(112, 'University of Nottingham Malaysia', 'Nottingham', 'Selangor', 100014, 2000, 'Private', 'The University of Nottingham Malaysia is a private university branch campus of the University of Nottingham. The campus is run as a company called The University of Nottingham Malaysia Sdn Bhd. The Malaysia campus was the first campus of a British university in Malaysia and one of the first to open outside Britain thus earning the distinction of the Queen\'s Awards for Enterprise 2001 and the Queen\'s Award for Industry (International Trade) 2006.', 'Semenyih, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(113, 'Monash University Malaysia', 'Monash', 'Selangor', 100014, 1998, 'Private', 'Monash University Malaysia, the Malaysian campus of Monash University opened in 1998 and it is the first foreign university in Malaysia. Established in 1998, Monash Malaysia is the third largest campus of Australia\'s largest university and the first foreign university campus in Malaysia that operates in partnership with the Sunway Education Group.', 'Bandar Sunway, Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia'),
(114, 'Xiamen University Malaysia', 'XMUM', 'Selangor', 100014, 2015, 'Private', 'Xiamen University Malaysia, abbreviated as XMUM, is the first China university overseas campus, set up by a renowned China\'s Xiamen University in Malaysia. Xiamen University Malaysia is wholly owned by China\'s Xiamen University which is directly under the administration of the China Ministry of Education. Xiamen University Malaysia is a high-level university under the national \"project 211\" and \"project 985\". ', 'Sunsuria City, Sepang, Selangor, 43900, Malaysia'),
(115, 'Universiti Putra Malaysia Kampus Bintulu (UPMKB)', 'UPMKB', 'Sarawak', 100013, 1986, 'Public', 'The Universiti Putra Malaysia Bintulu Campus (Malay: Universiti Putra Malaysia Kampus Bintulu or UPMKB) is a branch campus of Universiti Putra Malaysia located in Bintulu, Sarawak. The campus was reopened in November 2001 based on the third objective of UPM\'s 2001-2010 planning strategy, which is to upgrade UPM\'s ability as an internationally acclaimed Centre of Study, Agricultural and Biosource Services.', 'Jalan Nyabau, Peti Surat 396, 97008 Bintulu, Sarawak'),
(116, 'HELP Academy', 'HA', 'Kuala Lumpur', 10004, 1986, 'Private', 'Located at Damansara Heights in Kuala Lumpur, HELP Academyâ€™s campus consists of 2 blocks which are Wisma HELP and Kompleks Perdagangan Damansara (KPD).The strategic location in Damansara Heights provides many advantages such as easy access for residents from Petaling Jaya, Shah Alam and Klang and accessible to the many facilities such as shops, restaurants and cafes located in Bangsar.', 'Kompleks Pejabat Damansara\r\nKuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lumpur'),
(117, 'INTI International College Subang', 'IICS', 'Selangor', 100014, 1986, 'Private', 'INTI International University & Colleges are private university colleges located in Malaysia. The main campus was initially known as INTI University College until 31 May 2010 when the Higher Education Ministry announced its upgrade to university status. It is owned by INTI Education Group which has formalised its partnership with Laureate International Universities in 2008.', '3, Jalan SS 15/8, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor'),
(118, 'Kolej Unikop', 'UNIKOP', 'selangor', 100014, 1996, 'Private', 'UNIKOP College is wholly-owned by The Royal Malaysian Police Cooperation and was established in 1996 and its new Head Quarters located at Multimedia Super Corridor Park in Cyberjaya, Selangor Darul Ehsan. During its 22 years of existence, UNIKOP College has been given a full trust from the University of Technology MARA (UITM) to carry out pre-Diploma and Diploma programs in various fields of specialization.', 'Block 3420, Persiaran Semarak Api,\r\nCyber 4, 63000 Cyberjaya, Malaysia');
